HEADWORD: Woolding
<hw>Woold"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>The act of winding or wrapping anything with a rope, as a
mast.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A rope used for binding masts and
spars.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wool-dyed</ent>⟦br⟧
